metadata.experiment: Movement vocabulary experiment: 28 concepts x 5 languages x 5 models

semantic_coherence.description: Semantic clusters grouped by movement type. Mann-Whitney U tests and Cohen's d effect sizes compare fast vs slow speed concepts on key behavioral metrics.

cross_language_functor.description: For each concept, behavioral vectors (speed, dx, PLV, entropy, straightness, yaw) are averaged per language, then compared via CV and cosine similarity across languages. Functor faithfulness is the mean cosine similarity across all concept x language-pair combinations.

weight_space_geometry.description: PCA of 700 6D weight vectors; attractor analysis via greedy cosine-similarity clustering (threshold 0.9); Pearson correlations between each weight position and key behavioral metrics.

archetype_candidates.method: K-means clustering on normalized behavioral vectors (6 key metrics), k selected from [4-8] by pseudo-silhouette score.

archetypes.name: pacer
archetypes.description: Behavioral archetype with high path_straightness, high phase_lock_score, low mean_speed

archetypes.name: spinner
archetypes.description: Behavioral archetype with low yaw_net_rad, high dx, high contact_entropy_bits

archetypes.name: wobbler
archetypes.description: Behavioral archetype with low dx, low phase_lock_score, high contact_entropy_bits

archetypes.name: crawler
archetypes.description: Behavioral archetype with low phase_lock_score, low mean_speed, high path_straightness

archetypes.name: dasher
archetypes.description: Behavioral archetype with high mean_speed, high contact_entropy_bits, low phase_lock_score

top_findings: Fast vs slow concepts show Cohen's d = 0.599 on mean_speed (fast mean: 0.2049, slow mean: 0.1190)
Overall functor faithfulness (cross-language behavioral consistency): 0.8477 mean cosine similarity across 280 language-pair comparisons
PCA of weight space: PC1 explains 37.1%, PC2 explains 22.4% of variance (cumulative 2D: 59.4%)
Found 43 weight-space attractors (cosine > 0.9, size >= 3). Largest attractor has 74 trials
Fast vs slow on mean_speed: Cohen's d = 0.599 (medium effect)
Fast vs slow on dx: Cohen's d = -0.169 (small effect)
Fast vs slow on contact_entropy_bits: Cohen's d = 0.597 (medium effect)
